heading_context: Spinal conditions, injuries or spinal surgery and driving
chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have a spinal condition or an injury to your spine.
chunks.plain_content:
Spinal conditions, injuries or spinal surgery and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have a spinal condition or an injury to your spine.

heading_context: Spinal conditions, injuries or spinal surgery and driving
chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Spinal conditions, injuries or spinal surgery and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

heading_context: Spinal conditions, injuries or spinal surgery and driving
chunks.html_content:
If you’ve had spinal surgery, check with your doctor before you start driving again.

Fill in form G1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
